Green Life NYC food service is really good. The food is great and personally, the customer service I’ve received has been second to none. I’ve specifically been provided special hands on customer service from a representative by the name of Einym. She/he has gone above and beyond to service me and keep me happy. My food allergy concerns are always taken into consideration and also my food preferences. Whenever there’s an issue with my food or the time it takes to be delivered, Einym has always prioritized my concerns and has provided me the most exceptional customer service I have ever received in my lifetime. Because of this amazing customer service alone, is the main reason why I have continued my meal plans with green life nyc. I can directly get in contact with Einym and Einym responds to me in a timely fashion and is always courteous, respectful, empathetic and professional. I am not sure if Einym’s superiors understand how much of an asset he/she is but I can assure you, I value Einym’s service and can’t imagine dealing with anyone else. Einym should be considered for a promotion as I feel she has made an extreme impact on the company through individual effectiveness. Kudos to Einym. I thank Einym for all he/she has done for me and I look forward to continue doing business with this professional!

First. Extremely unprofessional If I can put negative stars I would. If you prepaid for food and specifically state YOU ARE ALLERGIC TO FISH AND GET SENT FISH, you are basically not completing a paid order and owe said meals.  Secondly. They claim to be a door to door delivery service and they are not. You have to adhere to how the Delivery man decides to deliver your food on that day. For example: Monday morning since he has to collect payment he came right to the door. (And he stole my change)  Tuesday morning driver was acting worried about getting a ticket from a invisible Traffic officer and made me come to my courtyard.  Wednesday morning same act now driver did not leave his car until i walked halfway to him. Also received fish and notified GreenLife  Thursday morning made me get closer to his vehicle basically to the curb.  Today Friday morning I received a call from the driver stating that i have to meet him at his vehicle because it is raining!!! Again received fish.  I called GreenLife to address these concerns and I was immediately meet with instant denial “We have never had these issues before” was the response to my quarrel.  My whole thing is if you claim to be a door to door service fulfill that claim, and if you’re a food prep service you have to pay attention to food allergies that is all. The food was great and I really liked it but the service is appalling unfortunately.

When I first joined a year ago I’d get my meals by 7:30 am... now it’s 9:35 and I’m still waiting. I would have appreciated a heads up in the change on schedule so I could decide if it works for me or not.  It does exactly what is advertised. You can tell they’re not improvising: Food is healthy, no complaints on the flavor department, perfect portions and delivery is always, always on point. It’s also far less expensive than ordering around while trying to eat healthy.

It has been nearly three and a half months since I began ordering my meals from Green Life. At the time, I knew I needed to make some changes in my lifestyle. I was nearly 220 pounds, an all-time high for me. Furthermore, my mother was diagnosed with diabetes — a disease that almost every family member of mine has battled. The news prompted me to get a physical done. It was during this physical I was notified of having an elevated a1c, in the pre-diabetic range. Shortly after being told this, I took charge of wanting — and needing — a healthier lifestyle. Since joining, I have lost nearly 30 pounds and have lowered my a1c levels. The Meals Very tasty and fresh. The basic plan includes three main course meals, along with two small snacks. The meals also come with a nutrition label that is extremely helpful for me, as I track my meals in the myfitnesspal app and share the insight with my dietitian on a bi-weekly schedule. Whenever I have a question regarding my order, the owners are quick to respond and maintain open communication. While I am not at my ideal weight and health, I know I am on the right path. For anyone looking to live a healthier life, don't think twice about trying this fantastic company! You won't regret it!
